Division Two was primarily played in Glasgow, with one game being played at RAF Lossiemouth for security reasons. Italy were absent, having been promoted to Division One. Greece made their return to Division Two after a six-year absence, whilst the tournament saw the international debuts of Guernsey and Jersey . It was won by Norway , Norway promoted to 2008 Division One. The win also granted them entry into 2008 WCL Division Five alongside runners-up Jersey and 3rd place Germany. Israel relegated to playoff with 2007 ECC Division Three winner. Greece came in last place and were relegated later was stripped of their first round points due to fielding ineligible players.
